<p>
  When I'm sent art (all mediums and creativity types) through direct/instant messaging, I feel like I'm obligated by both social norms and the UI/UX of instant messaging to externally validate the art I've been sent <i>as soon as I'm physically able to reply, and <b>before I'm allowed to continue conversing with you about other things.</b></i>
</p>
<p>
  This is a problem, because sometimes, I <i>do</i> get a free moment and finish obligated work, but <b><i>I'm not necessarily feeling well emotionally</i></b> and don't have the spirit to react to, or externally validate, others' creative output.
</p>
<p>
  If you need instant positive-reinforcement or critique on artwork, try a sizeable art-focused group chat, messaging server, or online forum, where anyone who is online and in the right mind can provide the engagement/reaction/insight you seek. <i>Way less pressure than a one-on-one DM!</i>
</p>
<p>
  Again, feeling gated into providing positive-reinforcement or insightful critique on other's creativity ASAP or <i>before I'm allowed to continue/topic-shift a conversation</i> stops me in place, especially when I'm not feeling well. If it's specifically <i>me</i> you'd like to share your work with, please provide me an <b><i>asynchronous</i></b> way to consume/react to your creative output. Asynchronous examples of sharing your work with me include basically anything where I can come and interact with your work in my own time, and <b><i>not</i></b> as a <i>chronological prerequisite</i> to any other interactions I'd like to have with you.
</p>
<p>
  Including:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Newsletters</li>
  <li>{% emailLinkPair nameStrings.contactEmail %}E-Mail{% endemailLinkPair %}</li>
  <li>Personal Sites</li>
  <li>Blogs</li>
  <li>RSS feeds</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <i>There is <b>one</b> exception to this ruleâ€¦ <b>If I'm allowed to reply-to/engage-with your art asynchronously!</b></i> In which case, feel free to DM it.<br>
  <i>What do I mean by asynchronous replying?</i>
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Replying to art sent to me whenever I like.</li>
  <li>Not replying to art sent to me at all. (Typically because of mental health.)</li>
  <li>Topic-switching from art you sent me (seemingly ignoring it) only to come back and respond to said art later, or via a different means of communication. (IE: You Discord me art, I seemingly ignore it, but respond on Bluesky for some reason.)</li>
</ul>

